Description:
    Creates HTTP cache headers configuration for your Folio application.

    This generator creates a cache_headers.rb initializer with default configuration.
    The cache headers system is automatically enabled through Folio::ApplicationControllerBase.

Example:
    bin/rails generate folio:cache_headers

    This will create:
        config/initializers/cache_headers.rb

Configuration:
    After running the generator, you can customize the cache behavior by:
    
    1. Adjusting settings in config/initializers/cache_headers.rb
    2. Overriding set_cache_control_headers method in specific controllers
    
    For emergency cache control, set environment variable:
    - FOLIO_CACHE_TTL_MULTIPLIER=0 to disable all caching
    - FOLIO_CACHE_TTL_MULTIPLIER=0.5 to halve cache times
    - FOLIO_CACHE_TTL_MULTIPLIER=2.0 to double cache times
